{"meta":{"sessionId":"c6793f45-3689-4c01-ae7d-54f90f5b78e0","learnerId":"learner-6266a062ce69","labId":"turn-heading-check-into-first-test","createdAt":"2026-07-12T06:11:14.186Z"},"events":[{"type":"session.started","lessonId":"turn-heading-check-into-first-test","learnerId":"learner-6266a062ce69","variantId":null,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:11:15.093Z","v":2},{"type":"learner.goal.stated","text":"Hi! I'm Maya, I do manual QA. Every release I check by hand that the community garden page shows the right heading. My team lead wants me to turn that manual heading check into an automated Playwright check, and write it myself. I've never written an automated test before, so I'll need some guidance.","timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:12:30.596Z","v":1},{"type":"ui.state.reported","activeApp":"Trellis Guide","openWindows":["Trellis Guide"],"editorFile":null,"editorDirty":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:12:30.612Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":1,"strategy":"orient","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:12:30.620Z","v":2},{"type":"intervention.proposed","triggerType":"inactivity","suggestedHintLevel":0,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:16:30.924Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":2,"strategy":"point-to-tool","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:16:30.931Z","v":2},{"type":"file.changed","path":"tests/heading.spec.js","timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:18:18.326Z","v":1},{"type":"intervention.proposed","triggerType":"tests_not_run","suggestedHintLevel":2,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:19:18.369Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":3,"strategy":"point-to-location","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:19:18.387Z","v":2},{"type":"intervention.proposed","triggerType":"inactivity","suggestedHintLevel":0,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:24:04.952Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":4,"strategy":"explain-concept","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:24:04.969Z","v":2},{"type":"learner.question","text":"I wrote my check and saved the file. But in the terminal, I type npm test and press Enter and nothing runs - the cursor just blinks. My question text also ended up stuck on the prompt line. How do I run npm test in this terminal?","stuck":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:24:36.209Z","v":1},{"type":"ui.state.reported","activeApp":"Trellis Guide","openWindows":["Trellis Guide"],"editorFile":"tests/heading.spec.js","editorDirty":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:24:36.218Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":5,"strategy":"faq-answer","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:24:36.229Z","v":2},{"type":"learner.question","text":"Ohh, I see it now. In my manual checklist every step has an expected result. My code line only FINDS the heading - it never states the expected result. That's like writing a test step with no \"expected\" column. I'll add the expect(...).toBeVisible() part from the README around my finder.","stuck":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:27:06.320Z","v":1},{"type":"ui.state.reported","activeApp":"Trellis Guide","openWindows":["Code Studio","Trellis Guide"],"editorFile":null,"editorDirty":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:27:06.337Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":5,"strategy":"faq-answer","contextManifest":{"included":[],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:27:06.345Z","v":2},{"type":"file.changed","path":"tests/heading.spec.js","timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:28:33.977Z","v":1},{"type":"checkpoint.evaluated","checkpointId":"first-authored-check","passed":true,"incomplete":[],"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:29:31.233Z","v":1},{"type":"checkpoint.completed","checkpointId":"first-authored-check","timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:29:31.243Z","v":1},{"type":"tests.completed","passed":1,"failed":0,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:29:31.471Z","v":1},{"type":"learner.question","text":"Honestly: the find-vs-check idea finally clicked and writing the test felt doable, but I lost a lot of time fighting the terminal (Enter never worked for me) and the windows hiding each other - the coaching was what got me through.","stuck":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:30:50.279Z","v":1},{"type":"ui.state.reported","activeApp":"Trellis Guide","openWindows":["Trellis Guide"],"editorFile":"tests/heading.spec.js","editorDirty":false,"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:30:50.287Z","v":1},{"type":"instructor.hint","level":0,"strategy":"faq-answer","contextManifest":{"included":[{"facet":"habit","id":"tests-before-done-rate","rule":"lesson-concept-habit"},{"facet":"habit","id":"recovery-after-failure-rate","rule":"domain-general"},{"facet":"calibration","id":"self-assessment","rule":"any-samples"}],"budgetChars":1400,"truncated":false},"timestamp":"2026-07-12T06:30:50.296Z","v":2}]}